					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842" rend="visible">
						<summary>Maimonides' Commentary on Seder Zera῾im in Judeo-Arabic.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842">
							<locus from="1r" to="228v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Seder zera῾im </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש סדר זרעים</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="en">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204 </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="he">משה בן מימון, 1138-1204 </persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th and 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>228 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>240</height>
										<width>190</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>175</height>
										<width>120</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>228 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each, numbered with Hebrew letters and marked by catchwords at the end. </p>
									<p>The volume is made up of fragments, of which folios 39-212 form the largest, of 16 quires.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning (folio 1 largely mutilated).</p>
									<p>Many pages water-stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="23 24" writtenLines="23 24">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Chapter numbers given in large square characters.</p>
									<p>Marginal notes.</p>
									<p>Dark red ink design next to the chapter number (folio 23v).</p>
									<p>Diagrams (e.g. 49r, 51v).</p>
									<p>Leaf catchwords between folios 3v-27v.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Yemenite square and semi-cursive script of the 15th nad 16th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="39r" to="212v"/> due to the 15th century hand, the rest of the volume belongs probably to the 16th century.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>An owner's note in Arabic characters, partly erased: folio 225v.</p>
							<p>Folios 1, 2, 226, 227 contain parts of the Commentary on the Pentateuch by Bahya ben Asher, covering verses from Numbers 11, Deuteronomy 23, 22 and 28.</p>
						</additions>
